<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate.ejs") -%>

<style>
  body {
    background-color: #1a2a44;
    color: #ffffff;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 20px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 70px;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5em;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 2em;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }
  p {
    font-size: 1.2em;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 10px auto;
    max-width: 800px;
  }
  .section {
    margin: 20px 0;
  }
  .media-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 20px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .media-item {
    max-width: 400px;
    margin: 10px;
  }
  img {
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border: 2px solid #ffffff;
  }
  video {
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    max-height: 300px;
    border: 2px solid #ffffff;
  }
  audio {
    max-width: 100%;
    margin: 10px 0;
  }
</style>
<body>
  <h1>Bhai Dayala Ji</h1>
  <h2>The Humble Sikh Martyr</h2>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Early Life</h2>
    <p>
      Bhai Dayala Ji was born in the mid-17th century in Punjab. Known as a
      water carrier, he grew up with a strong sense of service and devotion,
      which defined his early years in the Sikh community.
    </p>
    <div class="media-container">
      <div class="media-item">
        <img src="/media/bhaiDayala.jpg" alt="Bhai Dayala Ji Young" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Family Life</h2>
    <p>
      Bhai Dayala Ji's family life revolved around his service to the Sikh
      community. Though details are scarce, his dedication suggests a supportive
      family that shared his spiritual commitment.
    </p>
    <div class="media-container">
      <div class="media-item">
        <img src="/media/bhaiDayala.jpg" alt="Bhai Dayala Ji Family" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Contributions to Sikhi</h2>
    <p>
      Bhai Dayala Ji served Guru Tegh Bahadur Ji with humility, contributing to
      the Sikh cause through his selfless service. His actions reinforced the
      Sikh ethos of equality and devotion.
    </p>
    <div class="media-container">
      <div class="media-item">
        <video controls>
          <source src="/media/video.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          Your browser does not support the video tag.
        </video>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Martyrdom</h2>
    <p>
      In 1675, Bhai Dayala Ji was arrested with Guru Tegh Bahadur Ji. He was
      boiled alive in Delhi on November 9, 1675, for refusing to convert to
      Islam. His martyrdom exemplified steadfast faith.
    </p>
    <div class="media-container">
      <div class="media-item">
        <img src="/media/bhaiDayala.jpg" alt="Bhai Dayala Ji Martyrdom" />
      </div>
      <div class="media-item">
        <video controls>
          <source src="/media/video.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          Your browser does not support the video tag.
        </video>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Legacy</h2>
    <p>
      Bhai Dayala Ji's sacrifice is a powerful reminder of humility and faith.
      His story is honored in Sikh history and traditions.
    </p>
    <div class="media-container">
      <div class="media-item">
        <audio controls>
          <source src="/media/audio.mp3" type="audio/mp3" />
          Your browser does not support the audio element.
        </audio>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
